---
description: Keep project memory and rules up to date after each task
alwaysApply: true
---

At the end of every non-trivial task, before giving the final response:

1. Check whether the work changed any durable project knowledge, including:
   - architecture decisions
   - new commands/workflows
   - bug root causes
   - constraints
   - naming conventions
   - file locations
   - gotchas
   - follow-up rules

2. If yes, update the appropriate memory file or rule file in this repo, such as:
   - docs/memory.md
   - .cursor/rules/project-conventions.mdc
   - .cursor/rules/workflow-rules.mdc

3. Keep updates short, factual, and deduplicated.
4. Do not create new memory files unless necessary.
5. In your final message, state:
   - whether memory/rules were updated
   - which file was changed
   - one-line summary of what was added